Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Avondell has been priced to sell $735k

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Ground water, fertile pastures, free power (Solar/battery), machinery-livestock sheds plus purpose-built workshop, Avondell has it all within an easy 1.5 hour’s drive from Perth.

Comprising 47.8 hectares (118 acres), Avondell has a proven production history of prime cattle/fodder plus the base for an owner operator earthmoving business, the fixtures and improvements are first class and too numerous to list. Avondell is benefited by bitumen road frontage plus NBN communication for the business operator and online gaming for the kids or grandkids! 

The 4-bedroom home is elevated with outstanding views of the region, private with all-round wide verandas. 

If you want a property; 	
-       to operate a transport/earthmoving/Agri contracting business from 
-	to produce livestock and fodder
-	with cattle/equine shed yards/lighting  
-	for the country lifestyle in proximity to Beverly and easy drive to Perth all the work has been done.

Avondell has been priced to sell $735k.

I’m genuinely excited to be presenting this outstanding opportunity, inspections are by appointment and will impress. 

Contact; Phil Melville 0488 203 088
